# if -- conditional evaluation

- _if(self, whenTrue, whenFalse)_

If _self_ is _true_ answer the result of  _value(whenTrue)_, else answer _value(whenFalse)_.

Ordinarily _whenTrue_ and _whenFalse_ are literal no-argument procedures written using [Trailing Procedure Syntax].

* * *

See also: _ifFalse_, _ifNil_, _ifTrue_
